value.value: A molecular abnormality indicating the presence of an abnormally high level of the G1/S-specific cyclin-D2 protein.
Leukemia that occurs in a pig.
A beta thalassemia resulting from an unequal crossover/recombination event involving portions of the delta and beta globin genes, resulting in underproduction of the abnormal delta-beta globin.

A type of xeroderma pigmentosum resulting from mutation(s) in the POLH gene, encoding DNA polymerase eta. This form of the disease is characterized by normal DNA excision repair, but defective post-replication repair of DNA at UV-damaged sites.
A molecular abnormality indicating the presence of an abnormally high level of the G1/S-specific cyclin-D3 protein.
A blood concentration of prostate specific antigen greater than 0.03 ng/mL.
A change in the nucleotide sequence of the ERBB3 gene that that results in constitutive activation of receptor tyrosine-protein kinase erbB-3 and its downstream signaling pathways.

label.value: Primary Cutaneous B-Cell/T-Cell (Non-MF/SS) Lymphoma TNM Finding v8

value.value: A finding about one or more characteristics of primary cutaneous B-cell/T-cell [non-mycosis fungoides/Sezary syndrome (non-MF/SS)] lymphoma, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v8 classification system. There is no stage group system for non-MF/SS primary cutaneous lymphomas- including cutaneous T-cell, B-cell, and NK-cell lymphomas. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Primary Cutaneous B-Cell/T-Cell (Non-MF/SS) Lymphoma Distant Metastasis TNM Finding v8

value.value: A finding about one or more characteristics of primary cutaneous B-cell/T-cell (non-MF/SS) lymphoma, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v8 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Primary Cutaneous B-Cell/T-Cell (Non-MF/SS) Lymphoma M0 TNM Finding v8

value.value: No evidence of extracutaneous non-lymph node disease. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Primary Cutaneous B-Cell/T-Cell (Non-MF/SS) Lymphoma M1 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Extracutaneous non-lymph node disease present. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Primary Cutaneous B-Cell/T-Cell (Non-MF/SS) Lymphoma Lymph Nodes TNM Finding v8

value.value: A finding about one or more characteristics of primary cutaneous B-cell/T-cell (non-MF/SS) lymphoma, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v8 classification system as they pertain to staging of regional lymph nodes.

label.value: Primary Cutaneous B-Cell/T-Cell (Non-MF/SS) Lymphoma NX TNM Finding v8

value.value: Regional lymph nodes cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Primary Cutaneous B-Cell/T-Cell (Non-MF/SS) Lymphoma N0 TNM Finding v8

value.value: No clinical or pathological lymph node involvement. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Primary Cutaneous B-Cell/T-Cell (Non-MF/SS) Lymphoma N1 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Involvement of one peripheral node region that drains an area of current or prior skin involvement. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)
Describes a tumor or condition that develops, grows, or spreads rapidly.

label.value: Primary Cutaneous B-Cell/T-Cell (Non-MF/SS) Lymphoma N2 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Involvement of two or more peripheral node regions or involvement of any lymph node region that does not drain an area of current or prior skin involvement. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Primary Cutaneous B-Cell/T-Cell (Non-MF/SS) Lymphoma N3 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Involvement of central lymph nodes. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Primary Cutaneous B-Cell/T-Cell (Non-MF/SS) Lymphoma Primary Tumor TNM Finding v8

value.value: A finding about one or more characteristics of primary cutaneous B-cell/T-cell (non-MF/SS) lymphoma, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v8 classification system as they pertain to staging of the primary tumor (skin).

label.value: Primary Cutaneous B-Cell/T-Cell (Non-MF/SS) Lymphoma T1 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Solitary skin involvement. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Primary Cutaneous B-Cell/T-Cell (Non-MF/SS) Lymphoma T1a TNM Finding v8

value.value: Solitary lesion measuring less than 5 cm. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Primary Cutaneous B-Cell/T-Cell (Non-MF/SS) Lymphoma T1b TNM Finding v8

value.value: Regional skin involvement: multiple lesions limited to one body region or two contiguous body regions.  (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Primary Cutaneous B-Cell/T-Cell (Non-MF/SS) Lymphoma T2a TNM Finding v8

label.value: Primary Cutaneous B-Cell/T-Cell (Non-MF/SS) Lymphoma T2b TNM Finding v8

A loss of any arm of immune functions, resulting in potential or actual increase in infections. This state may be reached secondary to specific genetic lesions, syndromes with unidentified or polygenic causes, acquired deficits from other disease states, or as result of therapy for other diseases or conditions.

label.value: Primary Cutaneous B-Cell/T-Cell (Non-MF/SS) Lymphoma T2c TNM Finding v8

value.value: All disease encompassing in a 30-cm or more circular area. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Primary Cutaneous B-Cell/T-Cell (Non-MF/SS) Lymphoma T3 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Generalized skin involvement. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)
A plasma cell myeloma stage defined according to the Revised International Staging System (RISS) criteria.

A staging system for multiple myeloma based on the Revised International Staging System (RISS) criteria. This staging system does not apply to smoldering multiple myeloma (no AJCC staging system), monoclonal gammopathy of undetermined significance (no AJCC staging system), and Waldenstrom macroglobulinemia (no AJCC staging system). (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

Serum beta-2-microglobulin less than 3.5 mg/L and serum albumin 3.5 g/dL or more and no high-risk cytogenetics and normal LDH. High risk cytogenetics consist of one or more of the following: del17p, t(4;14), or t(14;16). (from AJCC 8th Ed.)
Not stage I or III. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

Serum beta-2-microglobulin 5.5 mg/L or more and high-risk cytogenetics and/or high LDH. High risk cytogenetics consist of one or more of the following: del17p, t(4;14), or t(14;16). (from AJCC 8th Ed.)
An indication that Epstein-Barr virus DNA has been detected in a sample.
A cytogenetic abnormality that refers to loss of all or part of the short arm of chromosome 4 (4p).
An indication that mutation, overexpression, or rearrangement of an Wnt gene family member has been detected in a sample.

A mesylate salt form of trioxifene, a nonsteroidal selective estrogen receptor modulator (SERM).  Trioxifene competitively inhibits the binding of estradiol to estrogen receptor alpha (ER alpha), resulting in ER alpha-mediated gene expression.  Clinical development of Trioxifene has not proceeded because of lack of superior results over tamoxifen and side effect profile. (NCI)
Having a severe and rapid onset of symptoms with short duration.
An indication that BK virus has been detected in a sample.
An indication that human herpesvirus 6 has been detected in a sample.
An indication that JC virus has been detected in a sample.
A molecular abnormality indicating rearrangement of the DDIT3 gene.
An indication that SLC45A2 expression has been detected in a sample.
An indication that hepatitis virus B has been detected in a sample.

label.value: PSA Level Less than Twenty Five

value.value: A blood concentration of prostate specific antigen less than 25 ng/mL.
An indication that SCGB2A2 expression has been detected in a sample.
An indication that UGT1A1*28 expression has not been detected in a sample.
Usually used to describe a condition that is persistent and long standing.

label.value: Simplified Preoperative Assessment for Appendix Tumor Score

value.value: A set of imaging criteria, based on preoperative CT scans, used to predict the likelihood for complete cytoreduction in patients with low-grade mucinous adenocarcinoma (LGMA) of the appendix. A score is determined by the presence of scalloping at 4 anatomic sites and the absence or presence of mesenteric foreshortening of the small bowel. A score under 3 is a significant predictor for complete cytoreduction.
A subjective score of 0 on a prognostic scale that ranges from 0 to 7.
